        "body": "## Summary\n\n- add a concise ClawHub plugin-development entry point that routes plugin and skill authors to the canonical OpenClaw guides and `openclaw/plugin-inspector`\n- link the ClawHub overview and validation-fix guidance to that handoff, and replace OpenClaw site-relative remediation links with canonical `docs.openclaw.ai` URLs\n- document the ownership boundary: ClawHub owns registry-specific docs while OpenClaw owns plugin runtime, SDK, and skill-authoring docs\n- preserve current `main`'s OpenClaw-hosted ClawHub docs sync model, leaving the removed ClawHub-local navigation and LLMS files deleted\n\nThe final PR diff is four docs files: 95 additions and 36 deletions.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `bun run ci:static` -> passed\n- current OpenClaw `scripts/docs-sync-publish.mjs` -> synced 20 ClawHub doc assets into the OpenClaw docs tree\n- current OpenClaw `scripts/check-docs-mdx.mjs <synced-clawhub-dir>` -> `Docs MDX check passed (17 files)`\n- synced `/clawhub/plugin-development` preview route -> HTTP 200\n- all 18 linked OpenClaw documentation pages and `openclaw/plugin-inspector` -> HTTP 200\n- `git diff --check` -> clean\n- `git merge-tree --write-tree origin/main HEAD` -> clean\n- trusted autoreview -> no accepted/actionable findings\n",
